Description: Small, hollow, breccia artefact in the shape of a cone with a pointed top. A pair of very small cylindrical holes appear at the lower base. The upper surface is covered in horizontal and vertical lines creating a pattern of rectangles.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), D14.20A, lowest floor
Bibliographic references: Spencer 1997 / Amara West I, The Architectural Report (p. 111)
